President Donald J. Trump spoke with President Moon Jae-in of South Korea to discuss the recent meeting between Moon and North Korean leader Kim Jong Un. Trump thanked Moon for their close coordination and committed to staying in contact in the coming weeks. Both leaders agreed that the pressure from the US, South Korea, and the international community has led to this significant moment. They emphasized that a peaceful and prosperous future for North Korea depends on its complete, verifiable, and irreversible denuclearization.